text: Jānis Cakuls (4 July 1926 – 26 February 2022) was a Latvian Roman Catholic prelate. He became a priest in 1949. He was titular bishop of Tinista and was auxiliary bishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Riga, Latvia, until 1993 when he resigned.Catholic-Hierarchy.org.-Janis Cakuls Cakuls died on 26 February 2022, at the age of 95. ==References== Category:1926 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Roman Catholic bishops Category:Latvian people
